description: Escutcheon with the title of the map of Southeastern France, No. 17 of "Nouvel Atlas Portatif" by Robert de Vaugondy, Paris, 1762.  The left bottom corner of the map.  A tablet with a moulded frame and vine decoration, rises in a landscape before barrels at left, a rock at right.
